node.text: This is a tough one and I expect it will cause some friction on my feed but it is a very necessary and important debate. I'm glad that @cnbc @sorkinsays and the #SquawkBox team have the guts to take on the issue. Regardless of your politics, how do you feel about any #socialmedia platform permanently banning a voice. Slippery slope?

node.text: The canary in the coal mine for the #economy has to be American #smallbusiness They create 60% of the jobs. I have witnessed an incredible turnaround in my private portfolio. My CEO's have performed the great #digital pivot and have built extremely high margin direct to consumer models over the last year and a half. Brian Sullivan and I go at it to "peel the onion" on this transformation, and yes there were winners and losers. #fastmoney #CNBC

node.title: Small Business Is The Canary In The Coal Mine For The American Economy

node.text: Corporate tax rates are how nations compete for business. The better run counties charge lower tax rates and get the jobs that help grow their economies. Trying to set a minimum corporate tax rate of 15% is just old fashioned price fixing. Its a very bad Idea. Let nations compete for capital and jobs. Competition and innovation is what keeps the economy growing not more taxes!

node.title: Price Fixing Corporate Tax Rates Is Bad For Our Economy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Kevin O'Leary on August 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Kevin O'Leary aka Mr. Wonderful @kevinolearytv Assholes get rich because they are not afraid to ask for what they want. wha'.

node.text:
If you don't ask for what you want, someone else will.

There’s a big misconception that to be a “nice person”, you’ve got to sit back and quietly accept whatever comes your way. I think that's a load of crap. Whether it’s your career, business, or life goals...YOU have to take control.

Now I'm not saying you have to be an asshole to get ahead in this wonderful game of business, but what I am saying is that there is something you can learn. Don’t sleep on your dreams, always speak up and ask for what you want, and don’t worry when they call you an asshole.

node.text:
I’m putting on my chef hat today to help you tackle a new recipe, but not the kind that is edible… I’m talking about building a proper pitch for investors. 

When building your pitch, think of it like a recipe:

[1] Start with base ingredients like your company vision and mission
[2] Add spices like financials and projections for flavor
[3] Cook it all up by practicing your narrative learning it inside and out
[4] Garnish with your own personality and flair to top it off

It’s that simple! 

Next Thursday, I’m hopping on with Ureeka for their quarterly pitch practice to deliver some recipe feedback to three entrepreneurs. 

Want to join in? Go to @ureeka.biz to get the full details. 

#mrwonderful #chefwonderful #entrepreneurship

node.text: The canary in the coal mine for the #economy has to be American #smallbusiness They create 60% of the jobs. I have witnessed an incredible turnaround in my private portfolio. My CEO's have performed the great #digital pivot and have built extremely high margin direct to consumer models over the last year and a half. Brian Sullivan and I go at it to "peel the onion" on this transformation, and yes there were winners and losers. #fastmoney #CNBC

node.text:
Felt cute, may delete later.

Major throwback to my hippie days on the way to university for my first term of classes, fall of 1973. I was taking Environmental Studies and I never DREAMED I would be wearing a suit to work every day. 

Just because I took courses on Environmental Studies didn’t mean I needed to stay in that particular field. The path is always yours to decide. 

Goals change, dreams change, people evolve….and I wouldn’t have it any other way. Now go create that path and blaze that trail 👊🏼

#tbt #mrwonderful #unclekevin #yougotthis
